12. Explain fully the circumstances of all payments, including the terms of any oral agreement or understanding pursuant to which they were made.
New York State United Teachers ("NYSUT") is a federation of more than 1,200 local unions
representing current and retired employees of New York's schools, colleges, and healthcare
facilities. NYSUT Member Benefits is a tax exempt, not for profit "rust established for the
exclusive benefit of the members of NYSUT. ING Life Insurance and innuity Company ("ILIAC") makes
a group annuity product ("Opportunity Plus") available to employees of school districts and public
universities in the State of New York specifically for members of NYSUT. Opportunity Plus is
primarily used to establish tax deferred annuities for school teachers under Section 403 (b) of the
Internal Revenue Code. By agreement with ILIAC, NYSUT Member Benefits endorsed the Opportunity
Plus program to NYSUT members and used its best efforts to identify NYSUT-sponsored events for the
purpose of allowing ILIAC to promote the Program. ILIAC also had access to NYSUT newsletters and
other communication facilities for purposes of promoting the Program The payments
detailed in this Part B were provided for under the terms of ILIAC': agreement with NYSUT Member
